cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new algorithm for training a re-weighted L2 Support Vector Machine (SVM), which is a popular machine learning technique used in various fields such as computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and data mining (cs.DS). The focus of the paper is on enhancing sparsity in SVM classifiers, which is a common goal in machine learning research and falls under the category of feature selection (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the proposed algorithm, which is relevant to the field of optimization (cs.NE). Additionally, the use of binary weights in the algorithm suggests a potential application in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
